---
description: Frontend security for Next.js
globs:
  - "frontend/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"
alwaysApply: true
---

- Never expose secrets; only use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` env vars for safe values.
- Avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`; if unavoidable, sanitize inputs.
- Prefer HTTP-only cookies for auth; avoid storing tokens in `localStorage`.
- Enforce Content Security Policy at the framework/proxy level.
- Validate and sanitize all user-provided data rendered in the UI.

